      "content": "that makes sense for the formal debate part. but i want to go deeper into the social aspect. one of the points i'm seeing in some old texts is the idea that segregation was actually \"good\" for preserving the unique cultural identities and traditions of different groups so they wouldn't get lost in a melting pot. can you expand on that? like, how would someone argue that racial segregation was actually a way to protect cultural heritage instead of just being about exclusion?",
